<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-12-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-12-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="360" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d360">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/3607</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Group</gloss> to
                                    the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">New
                                            York</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-12-02"><hi rend="italic">December 2,
                                        1921</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received December
                                3.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to our letter of November
                                    28th<note n="89" xml:id="d360fn89">Not printed.</note> with
                                respect to the proposed extension of the Pacific Development
                                Corporation loan to China, we beg to state that the Chinese
                                Government paid the interest <pb facs="0521" n="397" xml:id="pg_397"/> due the Corporation on December 1st, and the lending banks in the
                                American Group have approved the extension of the Corporation’s note
                                held by them for six months on the terms outlined in the two letters
                                of November 25th and November 28th from the Corporation to the
                                Group, copies of which are attached.<note n="90" xml:id="d360fn90">Not printed.</note></p>
                            <p>Respectfully,</p>
                            <closer><hi rend="smallcaps">J. P. Morgan</hi> &amp; Co.<lb/><hi rend="italic">For the American Group</hi></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>